steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"5l8ep","text":"Prepare surgical area in accordance with institutional requirements.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1l307","text":"- Clean and sterilize instruments","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8n78d","text":"- Warm heating pad","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a9grn","text":"- Check all equipment prior to starting","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"68kef","text":"- Lightly anesthetize mouse with Isoflurane","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b1bes","text":"- If using wired VMR, take down coil by carefully cutting sutures and unspooling wire. Take care not to cut the wire","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4mj08","text":"- Lubricate disposable gavage needle with Surgilube or similar and administer 100 uL water enema to remove fecal pellets","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"233b2","text":"- Insert balloon catheter to depth of 2 cm and secure in place by taping tubing to animal tail","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cqqrc","text":"- Place mouse into broomenator style restrainer and allow to wake up","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2oe6j","text":"- Follow manufactures instructions for recording EMG and pressure tracings","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4gj0u","text":"- We use a NeuroLog NL100AK headstage, Band-Pass Filter (NL125/6), Pressure Amp (NL108A), and Extracellular Recording Amplifier (NL104A) feeding into Spike2 for our wired recordings and the Data Sciences International Ponemah system for our wireless recordings","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aspod","text":"- Program barostat (Distended Series IIR) to deliver sequential balloon inflations of 20, 40, 50, 60, 70, and 80 mmHg for 20 s each with a 2 m rest period in between distensions","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9t65r","text":"Prepare the mouse","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2nn5n","text":"- Anesthetize with 1.5% inhaled Isoflurane","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"apmat","text":"- Shave neck and right abdomen","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bpr66","text":"- Clean exposed skin with Betadine","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bdmel","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2s2af","text":"Surgical incisions","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aj5fl","text":"- Make a small (\u003c 1 cm) skin incision in right lower abdomen above the inguinal region to expose the abdominal muscle","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8d1ro","text":"- Turn over mouse and make small incision on nape of neck","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"72bm9","text":"Wire Placement","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d98ao","text":"- Tunnel sterile cannula subcutaneously from neck incision along the side of the mouse and out the abdominal incision taking care to not injure/enter the abdominal compartment","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"284mq","text":"- Thread two sterilized EMG wires (~20cm length) through cannula. Holding the wires from the abdominal side, withdraw the cannula through the neck incision leaving the wires in place","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1oq7f","text":"- Remove 2-3mm of insulation from the abdominal end of the wires and tunnel into the abdominal muscle utilizing a 27g needle one at a time, ensuring the wires are close to each but do not touch","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"835s2","text":"- Secure wires using 6-0 non-dissolvable sutures","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6jeru","text":"- Close skin incisions with interrupted sutures","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2qdqv","text":"- Coil the wires extending from the next into a flat disc and suture to nape of neck to prevent disruption","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7k57f","text":"- Provide analgesia per institutional surgical protocol","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"52ikp","text":"- Administer 1ml of warm, sterile saline subcutaneously to mitigate dehydration","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b208b","text":"- Animals should be singly housed to prevent surgical site and EMG wire disruption prior to VMR experiment","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dmdnu","text":"- Prepare surgical area in accordance with institutional requirements.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"qbhs","text":"- Clean and sterilize instruments","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5f7i6","text":"- Warm heating pad","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"92jun","text":"- Check all equipment prior to starting","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c69pi","text":"Prepare the mouse","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c01l4","text":"- Anesthetize with 1.5% inhaled Isoflurane","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"62ohu","text":"- Shave right abdomen","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dqdmn","text":"- Clean exposed skin with Betadine","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a17b9","text":"Surgical incision","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dpv8v","text":"- Make a  ~ 1 cm skin incision in right lower abdomen above the inguinal region to expose the abdominal muscle sufficient to admit passage of the transmitter body","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e3ggt","text":"Transmitter Implantation","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"depmt","text":"- Use blunt dissection to create a pocket in the right flank sufficient to house the transmitter. Take care to avoid making the pocket too large, which could result in seroma formation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1g8kv","text":"- Remove 2mm of insulation from each wire. Set aside insulation for later use.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6t6eu","text":"- Using a 27 G needle, tunnel each wire individually through abdominal muscle. Wires should be placed closely together but should not touch","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2tgul","text":"- Place insulation back on the exposed ends of each wire as they emerge from the muscle tissue and secure in place with 6-0 non-dissolvable sutures. Note: the insulation can be stretched with fine forceps to aid placement back into the wire.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"34qjv","text":"- Suture the wires proximally to muscle entry to both secure the wires in place and to prevent moisture seepage into the transmitter.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"69nge","text":"- Close skin with either interrupted sutures or surgical staples","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"hm65","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
